Dependencies:

ruby 1.8.7
rubygems 1.3.5+
rails 2.3.4
mysql 5.x
apache 2.x + mod_rails (Passenger)
RHEL Unix packages: libxml2-dev, libxslt-dev, readline-devel, curl-devel
Ubuntu:  libcurl4-openssl-dev, libxslt-devel, libopenssl-ruby, libfreeimage-dev

Gems:
bundler 0.9.25
daemons

Apache:
  Add local site to /etc/hosts
  Create SSL keys
  Create VirtualHosts
    Example VirtualHosts:
    <VirtualHost *:80>
       ServerName dev.eternos.com
       DocumentRoot /Users/marcmauger/Documents/code/EDP/eternos/eternos.com/public
       RailsEnv development

       #ProxyPass / http://127.0.0.1:3000/
       #ProxyPassReverse / http://127.0.0.1:3000/
       #ProxyPreserveHost on
       Porter On
       PorterSharedSecret sh4mAlam4d1nGd0ng
       PorterPermission 0x0666

       RewriteEngine on
       RewriteRule ^/blog$ /Users/marcmauger/Documents/code/EDP/eternos/blog/blog/index.php [QSA]
       RewriteRule ^(/blog.*/$)$ /Users/marcmauger/Documents/code/EDP/eternos/blog/blog/index.php [QSA]
       RewriteRule ^/blog/?(.*)$ /Users/marcmauger/Documents/code/EDP/eternos/blog/blog/$1 [NC,QSA,L]
    </VirtualHost>
    
    <VirtualHost *:443>
      SSLEngine On
      ServerName dev.eternos.com
      RailsEnv development

      Porter On
      PorterSharedSecret sh4mAlam4d1nGd0ng
      PorterPermission 0x0666

      DocumentRoot /Users/marcmauger/Documents/code/EDP/eternos/eternos.com/public
    </VirtualHost>
    
  http://www.subelsky.com/2007/11/testing-rails-ssl-requirements-on-your.html
  
  
- Checkout source
- cd source dir
> bundle install

If error on taf2-curb install on Ubuntu, see:
 http://ruby.zigzo.com/2009/02/15/feedzirra-installation-errors/
 
- Copy config/*.yml.default to config/ & populate
- Create database.yml & workling.yml
- Create dev & test dbs
- Grant permissions on dbs
> rake db:auto:migrate


